## Installation & Setup

### Installation

```bash
# Kali Linux (pre-installed)
burpsuite

# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt-get install burpsuite

# Manual download
# Visit: https://portswigger.net/burp/
# Download and run installer
# java -jar burpsuite_community_linux_v2.xx.x.jar
```

### Initial Setup

```
1. Launch Burpsuite
2. Create new project or open existing
3. Go to: Proxy → Options
4. Default listening on: 127.0.0.1:8080
```

### Browser Proxy Configuration

#### Firefox Setup
```
1. Preferences → Network Settings
2. Manual proxy configuration
3. HTTP Proxy: 127.0.0.1
4. Port: 8080
5. Check "Also use for HTTPS"
```

#### Chrome Setup
```bash
# From command line with proxy
google-chrome --proxy-server=127.0.0.1:8080

# Or Settings → System → Proxy Settings (Windows)
```

### SSL Certificate Setup

```
1. Launch Burpsuite
2. Go to: Proxy → Options → CA Certificate
3. Export certificate (save as .crt or .pem)
4. Import to browser:

Firefox: Preferences → Privacy & Security → Certificates → Import
Chrome: Settings → Privacy and security → Security → Manage certificates
```

